{
  "texts": [
    "We conduct an experiment by setting n = 200, d = 16 in Equation 1, calculating the cumulative sum of eigenvalues of Ax for each sample, and averaging them to gauge its rank.",
    "As Figure 6(a) shows, it is noticeable that even on clean data that the attention module is most familiar with, it already exhibits a low-rank instance as the top 3% eigenvalues account for more than 85% energy.",
    "This bias amplifies as sensor data distortion intensifies.",
    "In other words, the matrix Ax, inherently low-rank due to multi-head operations, degrades when processing distorted data.",
    "However, this is not a consequence of low-quality input data since comprehensive fine-tuning can substantially mitigate this effect."
  ]
}